1.11 Part j
Create a function called evaluate.row(...) that takes one argument and returns “low” when the argument is less than 4, “mid” when the argument is between 4 and 7 (inclusive), and “high” when the arguement is 8 or larger. Then, use sapply(...) to apply it to column x1.
Solution:



Code
evaluate.row = function(val) {
  if (val &lt; 4) {
    return("low")
  }
  else if (val &lt;= 7) {
    return("mid")
  }
  else {
    return("high")
  }
}

(result = sapply(df$x1,evaluate.row))


 [1] "high" "low"  "mid"  "low"  "low"  "low"  "low"  "low"  "mid"  "low" 



In this instance, vectorization wouldn’t immediately simplify the logic of the condition, and abstracting this step within a function seems to be the most reasonable approach.

